value.name: Lighthouses in Portugal | Portugal Visitor - Travel Guide To Portugal
value.snippet: The Santa Marta Lighthouse in Cascais, west of Lisbon, on the Tagus Estuary, was built in 1868. Attractively colored in blue and white, the lighthouse is paired with the earlier Guia Lighthouse also in Cascais. Opened in 2007, the Santa Marta Lighthouse Museum was designed by architects Francisco and Manuel Aires Mateus.

value.name: Udsigtsplatform og restaurant i toppen af Lighthouse
value.snippet: På toppen af Lighthouse åbner en restaurant og en udsigtsplatform, hvor både beboere i Lighthouse og besøgende får mulighed for at nyde den exceptionelle udsigt til hele Aarhus og Aarhus Bugten. Restauranten og udsigtsplatformen er placeret på 44. etage i 142 meters højde.

value.snippet: The Tourlitis lighthouse, which is located at the northernmost extreme of the Cyclades archipelago, has been illuminating the route of seamanship for more than 120 years. The picturesque and impressive structure is amongst the few in Europe built on a rock in the sea.

value.snippet: Den nye del af Lighthouse består af tre bygninger - Fyrtårnet, Kanalhuset og Promenadehuset, som bliver fordelt på 40 boligeetager med 2-, 3-, 4- og 5-værelses lejligheder. Lejlighederne varierer i størrelse og indretning og giver dig mulighed for at få lige den lejlighed, som du drømmer om.

value.name: Lighthouse - OSRS Wiki
value.snippet: The Lighthouse is an area north of the Barbarian Outpost, and features prominently in the Horror from the Deep quest. The Lighthouse can only be entered during and after the quest; however, the island itself can be visited prior to starting the quest. Its dungeon is a popular place for players to kill dagannoth for Slayer.

value.name: Souter Lighthouse and The Leas | North East | National Trust
value.snippet: Opened in 1871, Souter Lighthouse was a marvel of its age and remains an iconic beacon. Hooped in red and white, it stands proud on the coastline midway between the Tyne and the Wear. It was the first lighthouse in the world designed and built to be powered by electricity.

value.name: Souter Lighthouse - Wikipedia
